[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/nymx 
		"nymx
	]a
	": Claiming for judging.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/nymx 
		"nymx
	]a
	": Ok...so I understand why this would irritate you, but remember...I never thought of it either. With all the experiences I have with graphical text adventures, the only thing to turn off the display was a command at a prompt. I would have never thought of just entering a blank command to disable it.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"So, just for my sanity...I checked the frame intervals for your keystrokes and they are spaced correctly. Yeah, there might be a one frame shorter command from time to time (like I find with Commodore games), but I'm not going to go through the entire game to find those instances. What you have here is fine. In addition to that, the short commands are also good. This was something also that I used a lot in my early play of these games. Because of your new discovery, I was curious as to why the first image showed up. Well, you discovery works after the game starts...where I would have thought a command or menu option would have been the trick.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I liked the previous TAS better, only because there was something to watch. But don't fret, as we have a new source of entertainment. A GEIGER COUNTER!
	$LF
]div
